	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Z80 is nor insanely slow, neither any slow.<br /><br />Comprasion for fastest methods of data copying on 6502 and Z80. 6502 is at 1.79MHz, which is more or less common for 6502-based system (C64 uses almost twice lower clock frequency, by the way), Z80 is at 3.5MHz, also quite common.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda $nnnn&nbsp; &nbsp;;4<br />sta $nnnn&nbsp; &nbsp;;4</div><br /><br />8t/byte<br /><br />1790000/8=223750 bytes per second<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">pop hl&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;;10<br />ld (nnnn),hl;16</div><br /><br />13t/byte<br /><br />3500000/13=269230 bytes per second

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


